does llama3 learn by itself?

No — same as before, Llama3 itself never learns or updates on its own. Its weights are frozen at whatever Meta trained it on.

• Every time you run `ollama run llama3` or use it in your RAG script, you get the exact same base model — no memory of past conversations, no self-updating

• Ollama doesn't retrain it in the background

• The only way it "gains" new knowledge is if you explicitly fine-tune it on new data (a separate, deliberate training process) — which isn't happening in your current setup

So right now: fully static model, zero self-learning, zero drift over time. Same behavior today as a year from now, unless you manually update to a newer model version.
                                                                                                                                                               
